1)	List the author id and name plus the books they’re written (title_id, title) and the books publisher name. 
Include authors that haven’t written a book, and books that haven’t been published. 
Note: You will need to insert values in some tables to confirm your query is correct – include the insertions as part of your solution.


SQL> INSERT INTO TITLES values
  2    ('T15','What Are The Next Applications?','history', 802, 29.99, 10467, 'P03','01-Feb-09',20000, 0.06);

1 row created.
SQL> INSERT INTO author_TITLES values ('T15','A01',1,1.0);

1 row created.

SQL>

select authors.Au_id, Fname, Lname, titles.title_id, title, publishers.pub_name from authors 
full outer join author_titles on  authors.au_id = author_titles.au_id 
full outer join titles on author_titles.title_id = titles.title_id 
full outer join publishers on publishers.Pub_id = Titles.Pub_id;


SQL> select authors.Au_id, Fname, Lname, titles.title_id, title, publishers.pub_name from authors inner join author_titles on  authors.au_id = author_titles.au_id right outer join titles on author_titles.title_id = titles.title_id inner join publishers on publishers.Pub_id = Titles.Pub_id;

